  "prompt": "What's a good video editor for windows?",
  "response": "There are several excellent video editing software options for Windows, depending on your needs and level of expertise. Here are some popular ones:\n\n1. **Adobe Premiere Pro**: A professional-grade video editor that offers a wide range of features and tools for advanced users. It's part of the Adobe Creative Cloud suite.\n\n2. **DaVinci Resolve**: Known for its powerful color correction and audio post-production capabilities, DaVinci Resolve is free to use and offers a professional version with advanced features.\n\n3. **HitFilm Express**: A free video editing software that also offers visual effects capabilities. It\u2019s great for beginners and intermediate users.\n\n4. **Filmora**: A user-friendly video editor that provides a variety of effects and templates. It\u2019s suitable for beginners and casual users.\n\n5. **Microsoft Photos**: This built-in app in Windows 10 and 11 has basic video editing capabilities, making it suitable for quick edits and simple projects.\n\n6. **CyberLink PowerDirector**: A powerful yet user-friendly video editor that offers a range of features, including 360-degree video editing and motion tracking.\n\n7. **OpenShot**: An open-source video editor that is free to use. It\u2019s easy to learn and has a good range of features for basic video editing.\n\n8. **Vegas Pro**: A professional video editing software that offers a wide range of features and is known for its intuitive interface.\n\nChoose one based on your experience level and the specific features you need!",
